-- BP Managers Plead Not Guilty to Criminal Spill Charges
-- B y   M a r g a r e t   C r o n i n   F i s k
-- 2012-11-28T21:42:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-28/bp-managers-plead-not-guilty-to-criminal-spill-charges.html
Two  BP Plc (BP/)  well-site managers and a
former executive pleaded not guilty to criminal charges growing
out of the 2010 Gulf of Mexico oil spill appeared in court to
enter pleas.  Robert Kaluza,  Donald Vidrine  and David Rainey entered
pleas today before U.S. District Judge Ivan L.R. Lemelle in New
Orleans.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Margaret Cronin Fisk in Detroit at 
 mcfisk@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Charles Carter at 
 ccarter12@bloomberg.net  